HEADWORD: Insuccation
<hw>In`suc*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insucare</ets>, <ets>insucatum</ets>, to soak in; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> + <ets>succus</ets>, <ets>sucus</ets>, sap.]</ety>
<def>The act of soaking or moistening; maceration; solution in the juice
of herbs.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The medicating and <qex>insuccation</qex> of seeds.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insuccess</ent>⟦br⟧
